@tootallnate/fmod-bank
=======================

This package's source code is MIT licensed. The bundled per-game
encryption-key list (`KNOWN_BANK_KEYS` in `src/decrypt.ts`) is
documented public knowledge sourced from the following OSS
projects:

- **CUE4Parse** (Apache License 2.0) —
  <https://github.com/FabianFG/CUE4Parse/blob/master/CUE4Parse/UE4/FMod/Fsb5Decryption.cs>
  Documents game→key mappings for the FMOD Studio bank XOR
  encryption scheme.

- **FMODBankDecryptor** (MIT) —
  <https://github.com/9382/FMODBankDecryptor>
  Reference C# implementation of the per-byte XOR + bit-reversal
  algorithm. Our `reverseBitsInByte` matches its `fourbitreverse`
  table behaviour bit-for-bit; the algorithm itself is
  trivially-reproducible from the format spec.

- **vgmstream** (ISC) —
  <https://github.com/vgmstream/vgmstream/blob/master/src/meta/fsb_keys.h>
  Adjacent reference for FSB-direct (not bank-level) keys. We
  don't include FSB keys (the sole layer of encryption Game Freak
  uses on Switch, for example, is at the bank level).

The keys themselves are not derived from any single commercial-
game extraction; they are documented public knowledge, refined by
many contributors over the years. Each entry includes the title
attribution from the source projects so users can cross-check.
